<p>Excellent. I've lately heard writing advice that says your character needs to want something in the first scene. This is a perfect example of that advice in action. Zyn doggedly pursues her goal, understanding the importance of pursuing smaller goals along the way, until such time when she finds something different but equally important to do. Very compelling stuff, and a good treatise on how to develop professional relationships.</p>

