<p>So if I get this correctly:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoiler(?)</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Or,&nbsp;did&nbsp;i&nbsp;get&nbsp;it&nbsp;wrong&nbsp;way?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This whole story is an allegory of writing a SCP on wiki:<br />
First you become member, but that's nothing outstanding. Then you get you first idea which get denied/downvoted. Then you start thinking. Looking for friends on site. Gaining experience. Learning tricks. Studying how to write. Soon, you become reckognizable among users. And then, you start writing your skip. Asking people for help/ideas/proofreading/etc.<br />
And finally, you have your first succesfull SCP.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
Please correct me if i'm wrong.<br />
Anyway, great tale. +1'd
